---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Words Containing AP — Scrabble Word List & Strategy"
  description="Complete list of Scrabble words containing AP with scores, definitions, and strategic tips. Find AP words for your next winning play."
  keywords="scrabble words containing ap, ap words scrabble, words with ap, scrabble ap word list, ap scrabble strategy"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Words Containing AP — Scrabble Word List & Strategy",
    "description": "Complete list of Scrabble words containing AP with scores, definitions, and strategic tips. Find AP words for your next winning play.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-14",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/words-containing-ap" }
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What are the highest-scoring AP words in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Top AP words include HAPPY (15 pts), PERHAPS (14 pts), CHAPTER (14 pts), CHAPEL (13 pts), and NAPKIN (12 pts). Double-P words score especially well." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How many valid Scrabble words contain AP?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Over 600 valid Scrabble words contain AP. It is a common and versatile pair appearing in words like CAP, MAP, HAPPY, CHAPTER, and ESCAPE across all lengths." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What short AP words are most useful?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Key short AP words include CAP (7 pts), MAP (7 pts), GAP (6 pts), LAP (5 pts), NAP (5 pts), RAP (5 pts), SAP (5 pts), TAP (5 pts), and ZAP (14 pts). ZAP scores highest due to the 10-point Z." }
      }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Words Containing AP — Scrabble Word List & Strategy</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-14">June 14, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>4 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">The AP pair is a common and productive combination in Scrabble. Found in everyday words like CAP, MAP, TAP, and HAPPY, it offers numerous scoring opportunities across all lengths. The P tile is worth 3 points, giving AP words a slight scoring edge over pairs with lower-value consonants. The -AP ending pattern is particularly flexible.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top AP Words by Score</h2>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
          <thead class="bg-gray-800">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">#</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Word</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Points</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Definition</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-800">
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">1</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">CHAPTER</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">14</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">A book section</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">2</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">PERHAPS</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">14</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Maybe</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">3</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">HAPPY</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">15</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Feeling joy</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">4</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">NAPPY</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">12</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">A diaper</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">CHAPEL</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">13</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">A small church</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">NAPKIN</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">12</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">A table cloth</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">TRAP</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">6</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">A catching device</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">8</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">CLAP</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">8</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">To strike palms</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">9</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">WRAP</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">9</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">To cover up</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">10</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">CAP</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">A head covering</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">11</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">MAP</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">A geographical chart</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">600+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid AP words</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">9 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Average score</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">Common</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Pair rarity</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">The -AP Ending Pattern</h2>

      <p>The -AP ending accepts many consonants, giving you quick plays when the board is tight. CAP, GAP, LAP, MAP, NAP, RAP, SAP, TAP, and ZAP provide options for every rack.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CAP</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">7 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">MAP</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">7 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TAP</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">5 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">WRAP</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">9 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TRAP</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">6 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CLAP</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">8 pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">🎯 Key Takeaway</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">AP is a <span class="text-white font-medium">reliable scoring pair</span> with 600+ valid words. The 3-point P adds value to every play. Focus on double-P words like HAPPY (15 pts) and NAPPY (12 pts) for high-efficiency scoring, and use short -AP words (CAP, MAP, TAP) for tactical board control.</p>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/words-containing-qu" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Words Containing QU — Essential Scrabble Q Words</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/words-with-multiple-vowels" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Words With Multiple Vowels — Scrabble Vowel Dumps</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/four-letter-words-every-player-should-know" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Four-Letter Words Every Scrabble Player Should Know</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-blue-800/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find every AP word from your tiles — instant results, no signup</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-400 text-gray-950 text-sm font-semibold transition-colors">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>